HEADWORD: Dulcified
<hw>Dul"ci*fied</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Sweetened;
mollified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Dulcified spirit</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Dulcified spirits</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a compound of alcohol
with mineral acids; <as>as, <ex>dulcified spirits</ex> of
niter</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulcifluous</ent>⟦br⟧
